      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d243n1-ptr" id="PJA04d243n1">1</a>
      
   <p>Not identified.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d243n2-ptr" id="PJA04d243n2">2</a>
      
   <p>Samuel Adams (<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> to James Warren, 30 July 1775, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-03-02-0061&amp;expandNote=PJA03d064n1#PJA03d064n1" class="document">note 1</a>, above).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d243n3-ptr" id="PJA04d243n3">3</a>
      
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s urgency in proposing relief for the Massachusetts delegates is perhaps underlined by his extravagance in having written Warren three letters within the space of four days, all of them taking less than two pages of sheets folded to make four pages eachthis at a time of acute paper shortage.</p>

